The paper presents efficient data structures for submatrix maximum queries in Monge matrices and Monge partial matrices, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses techniques for exploiting the structure of the upper envelope of Monge matrices, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also analyzes the number of breakpoints in the upper envelope of a Monge partial matrix, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also presents a constant query-time data structure with $O(n^{1+\varepsilon})$ construction time and space, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SC (Scientific Computing). Finally, the paper uses techniques from numerical analysis to analyze the complexity of the data structures, which suggests that it may belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
